    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred finely</p><p>Cut your<strong> avocado[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, around the <strong>stone[s]</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>stone[s]</strong> using a spoon, then scoop out the <strong>avocado flesh </strong>and dice roughly</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>remaining garlic</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>ranch-style dressing</strong></p>",
